ef%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fchcoc.gov%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2FOPM%2520Memorandum%2520re%2520Schedule%2520Policy%2520Career%2520Guidance%252001-27-2025.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eoriginally%20issued%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20January%2021.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESpecifically%2C%20the%20memo%20asked%20agencies%20to%20%26quot%3Bdetermine%20permanent%20worksites%26quot%3B%20for%20employees%20who%20have%20been%20working%20remotely%20full-time%20and%20include%20%26quot%3Bthe%20steps%20the%20agency%20will%20take%20to%20move%20these%20employees'%20duty%20stations%20to%20the%20most%20appropriate%20Federal%20office%20based%20on%20the%20employees'%20duties%20and%20job%20functions.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20returning%20to%20the%20office%20might%20be%20more%20straightforward%20for%20workers%20who%20live%20nearby%2C%20the%20memo%20also%20asked%20agencies%20to%20provide%20a%20description%20that%20justifies%20why%20employees%20who%20live%20more%20than%2050%20miles%20from%20existing%20worksites%20should%20receive%20relocation%20benefits.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAgencies%20should%20begin%20working%20on%20%26quot%3Bphasing%20in%20the%20return%20of%20remote%20workers%20who%20are%20more%20than%2050%20miles%20from%20a%20current%20agency%20office%2C%20which%20may%20present%20unique%20challenges%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20memo%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20workers%20might%20be%20eligible%20for%20exemptions%2C%20which%20the%20memo%20said%20could%20be%20due%20to%20disability%2C%20a%20qualifying%20medical%20condition%2C%20or%20%26quot%3Bother%20compelling%20reason%26quot%3B%20that%20an%20agency%20head%20and%20supervisor%20sign%20off%20on.%20OMB%20and%20OPM%20did%20not%20specify%20whether%20employees%20living%20more%20than%2050%20miles%20away%20from%20an%20office%20would%20receive%20or%20be%20considered%20for%20an%20exemption.%20Monday's%20memo%20requested%20a%20response%20to%20OMB%20and%20OPM%20no%20later%20than%20February%207.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOPM%20referred%20Business%20Insider%20to%20its%20initia